Name: if
Description: Conditional statement; Executes code block if condition is true; Returns Boolean decision result

Name: else
Description: Else block; Executes code if preceding if condition is false; Always paired with if

Name: else if
Description: Else if block; Tests additional condition if previous if was false; Allows multiple conditions

Name: switch
Description: Switch statement; Tests expression against multiple cases; More efficient than if-else chain

Name: case
Description: Case label in switch; Matches value against switch expression; Execution continues to next case if no break

Name: default
Description: Default case in switch; Executes if no other cases match; Optional but recommended

Name: break
Description: Break statement; Terminates loop or switch execution; Transfers control to statement after loop/switch

Name: for
Description: For loop; Iterates fixed number of times; Takes init, condition, increment; Best for counting loops

Name: foreach
Description: Foreach loop; Iterates over collection elements; Cleaner syntax than for loop for collections; Each iteration gets one element

Name: continue
Description: Continue statement; Skips current iteration; Continues with next iteration of loop; Ignores remaining code in current iteration

Name: return
Description: Return statement; Exits function immediately; Returns value to caller; Optional value if void function

Name: throw
Description: Throw statement; Throws exception; Transfers control to exception handler; Used for error handling

Name: SELECT
Description: SELECT statement; Retrieves data from one or more tables; Returns result set; Foundation of all queries

Name: FROM
Description: FROM clause; Specifies table(s) to query; Required in SELECT; Can include table joins

Name: WHERE
Description: WHERE clause; Filters rows based on conditions; Optional; Returns matching records only

Name: JOIN
Description: JOIN clause; Combines rows from multiple tables; Uses relationship keys; Returns matched records

Name: INNER JOIN
Description: INNER JOIN; Returns only matching records from both tables; Default JOIN type; Excludes unmatched rows

Name: LEFT JOIN
Description: LEFT JOIN; Returns all rows from left table plus matching from right; Includes unmatched left records with NULL

Name: GROUP BY
Description: GROUP BY clause; Groups rows by column values; Used with aggregate functions; Summarizes data

Name: HAVING
Description: HAVING clause; Filters grouped data; Works with GROUP BY; Like WHERE but for groups

Name: ORDER BY
Description: ORDER BY clause; Sorts result set; ASC (ascending) or DESC (descending); Affects result presentation

Name: LIMIT
Description: LIMIT clause; Restricts number of returned rows; Useful for pagination; Improves performance

Name: OFFSET
Description: OFFSET clause; Skips specified number of rows; Used with LIMIT for pagination; Enables paging

Name: INSERT
Description: INSERT statement; Adds new rows to table; Specifies columns and values; Creates new records

Name: UPDATE
Description: UPDATE statement; Modifies existing rows; Always use WHERE to target specific rows; Changes data values

Name: DELETE
Description: DELETE statement; Removes rows from table; Always use WHERE; Deletes data permanently

Name: CREATE TABLE
Description: CREATE TABLE statement; Creates new table; Defines columns and data types; Establishes structure

Name: ALTER TABLE
Description: ALTER TABLE statement; Modifies table structure; Adds/removes/changes columns; Changes constraints

Name: DROP TABLE
Description: DROP TABLE statement; Deletes entire table; Removes structure and data; Irreversible operation

Name: COUNT
Description: COUNT function; Counts number of rows; Returns integer; Ignores NULL values

Name: SUM
Description: SUM function; Sums numeric values; Returns total; Useful for financial calculations

Name: AVG
Description: AVG function; Calculates average; Returns decimal; Useful for analysis

Name: MIN
Description: MIN function; Returns smallest value; Useful for range analysis; Works with numbers and dates

Name: MAX
Description: MAX function; Returns largest value; Useful for range analysis; Works with numbers and dates

Name: AND
Description: AND operator; All conditions must be true; Narrows result set; Used in WHERE clause

Name: OR
Description: OR operator; At least one condition true; Broadens result set; Used in WHERE clause

Name: NOT
Description: NOT operator; Reverses condition logic; Returns opposite results; Used with other operators

Name: IN
Description: IN operator; Matches any value in list; Shorthand for multiple OR; Useful for filtering

Name: BETWEEN
Description: BETWEEN operator; Matches values within range; Inclusive on both ends; Useful for date/number ranges

Name: LIKE
Description: LIKE operator; Pattern matching on text; Uses % (wildcard) and _ (single char); Case-insensitive

Name: IS NULL
Description: IS NULL operator; Checks for NULL values; Not equal to empty string; Used for missing data

Name: IS NOT NULL
Description: IS NOT NULL operator; Checks for non-NULL values; Opposite of IS NULL; Filters out missing data

Name: DISTINCT
Description: DISTINCT keyword; Returns unique values only; Removes duplicates; Reduces result set size

Name: UNION
Description: UNION operator; Combines results from multiple queries; Removes duplicates; Columns must match

Name: SUBQUERY
Description: SUBQUERY; Query within query; Inner query executes first; Result used by outer query

Name: EXISTS
Description: EXISTS operator; Checks if subquery returns any rows; Returns TRUE/FALSE; Used with WHERE

Name: CASE
Description: CASE statement; Conditional logic in SQL; Returns different values based on conditions; Like IF-ELSE

Name: CAST
Description: CAST function; Converts data type; Changes column/value type; Useful for compatibility

Name: COMMIT
Description: COMMIT statement; Saves all changes permanently; Ends transaction; Changes are irreversible

Name: ROLLBACK
Description: ROLLBACK statement; Undoes all changes in transaction; Reverts to previous state; Restores data

Name: BEGIN TRANSACTION
Description: BEGIN TRANSACTION; Starts new transaction; Groups multiple SQL statements; Enables atomicity

Name: PRIMARY KEY
Description: PRIMARY KEY constraint; Uniquely identifies each row; Not NULL; Only one per table

Name: FOREIGN KEY
Description: FOREIGN KEY constraint; Links to another table; Maintains referential integrity; Enforces relationships

Name: UNIQUE
Description: UNIQUE constraint; Ensures all values are unique; Allows NULL; Prevents duplicates

Name: INDEX
Description: INDEX; Creates searchable index; Speeds up queries; Slows down INSERT/UPDATE; Improves performance

Name: RIGHT JOIN
Description: RIGHT JOIN; Returns all rows from right table plus matching from left; Opposite of LEFT JOIN

Name: CROSS JOIN
Description: CROSS JOIN; Cartesian product; Returns all combinations; No ON condition needed

Name: HAVING COUNT
Description: HAVING with COUNT; Filters groups by count condition; Common aggregate filtering; Used with GROUP BY

Name: LIKE PATTERN
Description: LIKE pattern matching; Wildcard '%' matches any chars; Wildcard '_' matches single char; Text search

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the schedule entry; System-generated GUID; Primary key

Name: StaffId
Description: Reference to the staff member; Links to staff records; Required for schedule assignment

Name: ShiftStart
Description: Scheduled shift start date and time; Must be before ShiftEnd; Required field

Name: ShiftEnd
Description: Scheduled shift end date and time; Must be after ShiftStart; Required field

Name: Hotel_StaffTaskAssignment
Description: Daily task assignments and work orders for hotel staff members

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the task assignment; System-generated GUID; Primary key

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to parent Hotel_StaffSchedule record; Associates task with a specific shift

Name: TaskDescription
Description: Description of the assigned task; Maximum 500 characters; Mandatory field

Name: IsCompleted
Description: Indicates whether the task has been completed; Default is False; Updated by staff upon completion

Name: Hotel_Supplies
Description: Hotel supplies master catalog (Food, Linens, Toiletries, Cleaning materials, etc.)

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the supply item; System-generated GUID; Primary key

Name: SupplyName
Description: Name of the supply item; Maximum 200 characters; Mandatory field

Name: Category
Description: Supply category (Food, Beverage, Linen, Toiletry, Cleaning, Equipment); Maximum 50 characters

Name: ReorderLevel
Description: Minimum stock level before reorder is triggered; Must be >= 0; Default is 10 units

Name: Hotel_SupplierOrders
Description: Purchase orders to suppliers for hotel supplies and inventory replenishment

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the supplier order; System-generated GUID; Primary key

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to parent Hotel_Supplies record; Identifies which supply item is being ordered

Name: OrderQuantity
Description: Quantity of items ordered; Minimum 1 unit; Required field

Name: OrderDate
Description: Date and time when order was placed; Defaults to current timestamp; Immutable after creation

Name: Hotel_InventoryMovement
Description: Inventory stock movements, adjustments, and consumption tracking

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the inventory movement; System-generated GUID; Primary key

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to parent Hotel_Supplies record; Tracks which item was moved or adjusted

Name: MovementType
Description: Type of movement (Receipt, Consumption, Adjustment, Transfer, Waste); Maximum 30 characters

Name: Quantity
Description: Quantity of items moved; Positive for receipts, negative for consumption; Required field

Name: Hotel_LoyaltyProgram
Description: Loyalty program structure, tiers, and earning rules configuration

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the loyalty program; System-generated GUID; Primary key

Name: ProgramName
Description: Name of the loyalty program; Must be unique; Maximum 100 characters; Displayed to guests

Name: PointsPerDollar
Description: Points earned per dollar spent; Minimum 0.01; Default is 1 point per dollar

Name: Hotel_LoyaltyMembers
Description: Loyalty program member registration and profile information

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the loyalty member; System-generated GUID; Primary key

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to parent Hotel_LoyaltyProgram record; Associates member with a specific program

Name: GuestId
Description: Reference to Hotel_Guests record; Links loyalty membership to guest profile; Required

Name: TierLevel
Description: Current membership tier (Bronze, Silver, Gold, Platinum); Default is Bronze; Determines benefits

Name: Hotel_LoyaltyPoints
Description: Loyalty points earning, redemption, and balance tracking transactions

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the points transaction; System-generated GUID; Primary key

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to parent Hotel_LoyaltyMembers record; Associates transaction with member account

Name: PointsAmount
Description: Number of points in this transaction; Positive for earning, negative for redemption; Required

Name: TransactionType
Description: Type of points transaction (Earn, Redeem, Expire, Bonus, Adjustment); Maximum 30 characters

Name: Hotel_LoyaltyRewards
Description: Catalog of loyalty rewards and benefits available for point redemption

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the reward; System-generated GUID; Primary key

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to parent Hotel_LoyaltyProgram record; Associates reward with a specific program

Name: RewardName
Description: Name of the reward (Free Night, Spa Credit, Room Upgrade, etc.); Maximum 200 characters

Name: PointsCost
Description: Number of points required to redeem this reward; Minimum 1 point; Required field

Name: Hotel_EnergyManagement
Description: Energy consumption tracking and management by room and common areas

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the energy record; System-generated GUID; Primary key

Name: RoomId
Description: Reference to room or area being monitored; Optional for common area energy tracking

Name: EnergyType
Description: Type of energy (Electricity, Gas, Water, HVAC); Maximum 30 characters; Required

Name: ConsumptionValue
Description: Energy consumption value in standard units (kWh, gallons, etc.); Minimum 0; Required

Name: Hotel_UtilityBilling
Description: Utility billing records and cost allocation to rooms or departments

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the utility bill; System-generated GUID; Primary key

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to parent Hotel_EnergyManagement record; Links billing to consumption data

Name: BillAmount
Description: Total bill amount in local currency; Minimum 0; Required field

Name: BillingPeriod
Description: Billing period description (e.g., 'January 2024', 'Q1 2024'); Maximum 50 characters

Name: Hotel_SecurityIncidents
Description: Security incident reporting, tracking, and resolution for hotel premises

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the security incident; System-generated GUID; Primary key

Name: IncidentType
Description: Type of incident (Theft, Disturbance, Fire Alarm, Medical, Unauthorized Access); Maximum 50 characters

Name: IncidentDate
Description: Date and time when incident occurred; Defaults to current timestamp; Required

Name: Description
Description: Detailed description of the security incident; Maximum 1000 characters; Required for documentation

Name: Hotel_AccessControl
Description: Room access control logs, key card events, and door monitoring

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the access log entry; System-generated GUID; Primary key

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to parent Hotel_KeyCards record; Links access event to a specific key card

Name: AccessTime
Description: Date and time of access attempt; Required; Read-only after logging; Used for security audits

Name: AccessResult
Description: Result of access attempt (Granted, Denied, Error); Maximum 20 characters; Required

Name: Hotel_EventBooking
Description: Event and banquet hall bookings for conferences, weddings, and functions

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the event booking; System-generated GUID; Primary key

Name: EventName
Description: Name or title of the event; Maximum 200 characters; Required for identification

Name: EventDate
Description: Scheduled date and start time of the event; Required for venue scheduling

Name: ExpectedAttendees
Description: Expected number of attendees; Minimum 1; Used for catering and seating arrangements

Name: Hotel_EventDetails
Description: Detailed event requirements including catering, equipment, and setup specifications

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the event detail record; System-generated GUID; Primary key

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to parent Hotel_EventBooking record; Associates details with specific event

Name: RequirementType
Description: Type of requirement (Catering, AV Equipment, Seating, Decoration, etc.); Maximum 50 characters

Name: Specification
Description: Detailed specification or notes for the requirement; Maximum 500 characters; Optional

Name: Hotel_ComplaintLog
Description: Guest complaints and issues tracking - captures all guest complaints for resolution and service improvement

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the complaint record. System-generated GUID that serves as the primary key. Used to track the complaint through its entire lifecycle from logging to resolution.

Name: GuestId
Description: Reference to the guest who filed the complaint. Links to the Guest profile for contact information and history. Essential for follow-up communication and personalized service recovery.

Name: ComplaintDate
Description: Date and time when the complaint was logged. Auto-populated with current timestamp. Used for SLA tracking and response time monitoring.

Name: ComplaintCategory
Description: Category of the complaint such as Room Cleanliness, Noise, Staff Behavior, Amenities, Food Quality, or Billing. Used for trending analysis and targeted improvement initiatives.

Name: Hotel_ComplaintResolution
Description: Child table for complaint resolution and follow-up - tracks the resolution process for each complaint

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the resolution record. System-generated GUID that serves as the primary key. Links to complaint for complete resolution history.

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to the parent complaint record (Hotel_ComplaintLog.Id). Establishes the relationship between the complaint and its resolution details.

Name: ResolutionDate
Description: Date and time when the complaint was resolved. Null until resolution is complete. Used to calculate resolution time and measure service recovery efficiency.

Name: ResolutionNotes
Description: Detailed notes describing how the complaint was resolved, what actions were taken, and any compensation provided. Critical for service recovery documentation and training purposes.

Name: Hotel_LostAndFound
Description: Lost and found items management - tracks items found or reported lost by guests throughout the property

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the lost/found item record. System-generated GUID that serves as the primary key. Used to track the item from discovery to return or disposal.

Name: ItemDescription
Description: Detailed description of the item including color, brand, size, distinguishing features. Must be detailed enough to identify and verify rightful owner claims.

Name: FoundDate
Description: Date and time when the item was found or reported. Auto-populated with current timestamp. Used for retention policy and eventual disposal scheduling.

Name: FoundLocation
Description: Location where the item was found such as room number, lobby area, restaurant, pool, gym. Helps in identifying potential owner based on guest location history.

Name: Hotel_CorporateAccounts
Description: Corporate account management - stores corporate client information for business travel and negotiated rates

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the corporate account. System-generated GUID that serves as the primary key. Used across all corporate bookings and billing.

Name: CompanyName
Description: Official registered name of the corporate client. Must be unique to prevent duplicate accounts. Used for invoicing, contracts, and official correspondence.

Name: ContactEmail
Description: Primary email contact for the corporate account. Used for booking confirmations, invoicing, and account-related communications. Must be valid business email.

Name: Hotel_CorporateRates
Description: Child table for corporate negotiated rates - stores special pricing agreements linked to corporate accounts

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the corporate rate record. System-generated GUID that serves as the primary key. Links rate to specific corporate account.

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to the parent corporate account (Hotel_CorporateAccounts.Id). Establishes the relationship between the account and its negotiated rates.

Name: RoomTypeId
Description: Reference to the room type for which this rate applies. Links to room type configuration. Allows different rates for different room categories per corporate agreement.

Name: NegotiatedRate
Description: Special negotiated nightly rate for this room type. Must be non-negative. Represents the contracted price between the hotel and corporate client.

Name: Hotel_GroupBooking
Description: Group bookings and block reservations - manages reservations for multiple rooms such as weddings, conferences, tour groups

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the group booking. System-generated GUID that serves as the primary key. Used to track the entire group reservation as a single entity.

Name: GroupName
Description: Name or identifier for the group such as 'Smith-Johnson Wedding', 'TechCorp Annual Conference', 'Asian Tours Group 5'. Used for easy identification and communication.

Name: TotalRooms
Description: Total number of rooms blocked for this group. Minimum 1 room, maximum 500 rooms. Used for inventory allocation and group rate calculations.

Name: GroupRate
Description: Special discounted rate applied to all rooms in the group block. Must be non-negative. Typically 10-30% below rack rate depending on group size and season.

Name: Hotel_TransactionLog
Description: Audit log for all transactions and changes - provides complete audit trail for compliance, security, and troubleshooting

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the transaction log entry. System-generated GUID that serves as the primary key. Immutable once created for audit integrity.

Name: TransactionType
Description: Type of transaction such as CREATE, UPDATE, DELETE, LOGIN, PAYMENT, REFUND. Read-only once logged. Used for filtering and reporting on specific transaction categories.

Name: TransactionTimestamp
Description: Exact date and time when the transaction occurred. Auto-populated and read-only. Critical for audit trails, security investigations, and chronological analysis.

Name: UserId
Description: Reference to the user or staff member who performed the transaction. Read-only for accountability. Links to staff profiles for security audit purposes.

Name: Hotel_GroupRoomAllocation
Description: Child table for group room allocation - tracks individual room assignments within a group booking

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the room allocation record. System-generated GUID that serves as the primary key. Links individual rooms to the group booking.

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to the parent group booking (Hotel_GroupBooking.Id). Establishes the relationship between the group and its individual room allocations.

Name: RoomId
Description: Reference to the specific room assigned to this group booking slot. Links to room inventory. Used for room blocking and availability management.

Name: GuestName
Description: Name of the guest assigned to this room within the group. May be blank until rooming list is finalized. Used for pre-registration and key preparation.

Name: Hotel_WakeUpCalls
Description: Wake-up call scheduling and tracking - manages guest wake-up call requests and their execution status

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the wake-up call request. System-generated GUID that serves as the primary key. Used to track request from scheduling to completion.

Name: RoomNumber
Description: Room number for the wake-up call. Must match an active occupied room. Used by operators to identify the guest and room to call.

Name: ScheduledTime
Description: Date and time when the wake-up call should be placed. Used by automated or manual systems to trigger the call at the correct moment.

Name: IsCompleted
Description: Indicates whether the wake-up call was successfully completed. Defaults to false. Set to true when guest answers or after maximum retry attempts.

Name: Hotel_DoNotDisturb
Description: Do Not Disturb status tracking - records guest DND preferences and room status for housekeeping coordination

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the DND record. System-generated GUID that serves as the primary key. Tracks the DND status change event.

Name: RoomId
Description: Reference to the room with DND status. Links to room inventory. Used by housekeeping to identify rooms that should not be serviced.

Name: ActivatedAt
Description: Timestamp when DND was activated. Auto-populated. Used to track how long a room has been on DND for security welfare checks.

Name: IsActive
Description: Current DND status for the room. True means DND is active, false means it has been deactivated. Defaults to true when record is created.

Name: Tenancy_Tenants
Description: Tenant master information and profile - stores core tenant identity and status for rental agreements

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the tenant record. System-generated GUID that serves as the primary key. Used across all tenant-related transactions, leases, and communications.

Name: FullName
Description: Complete legal name of the tenant as per official identity documents. Used for lease agreements, legal notices, and official correspondence. Maximum 200 characters.

Name: DateOfBirth
Description: Tenant's date of birth for age verification and identity confirmation. Required for legal agreements and KYC compliance. Must be 18+ years for lease eligibility.

Name: TenantStatus
Description: Current status of the tenant: Active, Prospective, Former, Blacklisted. Defaults to Active. Determines eligibility for new lease agreements and property access.

Name: Tenancy_TenantDocuments
Description: Child table for tenant identity and verification documents - stores Aadhar, PAN, Passport, and other official documents

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the document record. System-generated GUID that serves as the primary key. Links document to tenant profile.

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to the parent tenant record (Tenancy_Tenants.Id). Establishes the relationship between the tenant and their uploaded documents.

Name: DocumentType
Description: Type of identity document such as Aadhar, PAN, Passport, Driving License, Voter ID. Used for KYC classification and verification requirements.

Name: DocumentNumber
Description: Official document number as printed on the identity document. Must be unique across all tenants for the same document type. Used for verification and legal purposes.

Name: Tenancy_TenantContactInfo
Description: Child table for tenant contact details - stores multiple phone numbers, email addresses, and emergency contacts

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the contact record. System-generated GUID that serves as the primary key. Allows multiple contact entries per tenant.

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to the parent tenant record (Tenancy_Tenants.Id). Establishes the relationship between the tenant and their contact information.

Name: ContactType
Description: Type of contact: Mobile, Landline, Email, WhatsApp, Emergency. Used to categorize and prioritize communication channels.

Name: ContactValue
Description: The actual contact detail such as phone number or email address. Format validated based on ContactType. Primary contact used for lease notifications.

Name: Tenancy_TenantHistory
Description: Child table for tenant rental history - tracks previous rental addresses and landlord relationships

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the history record. System-generated GUID that serves as the primary key. Tracks each previous tenancy separately.

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to the parent tenant record (Tenancy_Tenants.Id). Establishes the relationship between the tenant and their rental history entries.

Name: PreviousAddress
Description: Complete address of the previous rental property including street, city, state, and postal code. Used for background verification and reference checks.

Name: TenancyDuration
Description: Duration of the previous tenancy in months. Minimum 1 month. Used to assess tenant stability and reliability for new lease approval.

Name: Tenancy_TenantReferences
Description: Child table for tenant references - stores previous landlord and personal references for background verification

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the reference record. System-generated GUID that serves as the primary key. Allows multiple references per tenant.

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to the parent tenant record (Tenancy_Tenants.Id). Establishes the relationship between the tenant and their references.

Name: ReferenceName
Description: Full name of the reference person such as previous landlord, employer, or personal reference. Used for verification calls and background checks.

Name: ReferencePhone
Description: Phone number of the reference person for verification contact. Must be valid and reachable. Used by property managers for background verification.

Name: Tenancy_TenantEmploymentInfo
Description: Child table for tenant employment and income verification - tracks employment details for creditworthiness assessment

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the employment record. System-generated GUID that serves as the primary key. Tracks current and past employment.

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to the parent tenant record (Tenancy_Tenants.Id). Establishes the relationship between the tenant and their employment information.

Name: EmployerName
Description: Name of the current or previous employer organization. Used for employment verification and income assessment for lease approval.

Name: MonthlyIncome
Description: Gross monthly income in local currency. Must be non-negative. Used to calculate rent-to-income ratio for lease eligibility (typically max 30-40% of income).

Name: Tenancy_TenantKYC
Description: Child table for Know Your Customer compliance - tracks KYC verification status and compliance requirements

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the KYC record. System-generated GUID that serves as the primary key. Tracks KYC verification workflow.

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to the parent tenant record (Tenancy_Tenants.Id). Establishes the relationship between the tenant and their KYC verification status.

Name: VerificationStatus
Description: Current KYC verification status: Pending, InProgress, Verified, Rejected, Expired. Defaults to Pending. Must be Verified for lease activation.

Name: VerificationDate
Description: Date when KYC verification was completed. Null until verification is finalized. Used for compliance audit trails and periodic re-verification scheduling.

Name: Tenancy_Leases
Description: Lease agreement master information - core lease records linking tenants to rental properties

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the lease agreement. System-generated GUID that serves as the primary key. Referenced by all lease-related child tables.

Name: TenantId
Description: Reference to the tenant (Tenancy_Tenants.Id) who is the lessee. Links the lease to the responsible party for rent payments and property obligations.

Name: StartDate
Description: Official start date of the lease agreement. Determines when tenant gains legal possession of the property and rent obligations begin.

Name: MonthlyRent
Description: Monthly rent amount in local currency. Must be non-negative. Base amount before any additional charges or utilities. Used for payment scheduling.

Name: Tenancy_LeaseTerms
Description: Child table for detailed lease terms and conditions - stores specific clauses and contractual obligations

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the lease term record. System-generated GUID that serves as the primary key. Allows multiple specific terms per lease.

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to the parent lease record (Tenancy_Leases.Id). Establishes the relationship between the lease and its specific terms and conditions.

Name: TermType
Description: Category of the lease term such as PetPolicy, ParkingRules, MaintenanceResponsibility, NoiseRestrictions. Used for organizing and filtering specific conditions.

Name: TermDescription
Description: Detailed text of the specific term or condition. Maximum 1000 characters. Becomes legally binding once lease is signed by both parties.

Name: Tenancy_LeaseDocuments
Description: Child table for lease agreement documents - stores signed copies and legal attachments

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the document record. System-generated GUID that serves as the primary key. Tracks each uploaded document separately.

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to the parent lease record (Tenancy_Leases.Id). Establishes the relationship between the lease and its associated documents.

Name: DocumentName
Description: Name or title of the document such as 'Signed Lease Agreement', 'Addendum A - Pet Policy', 'Move-In Checklist'. Used for document identification and retrieval.

Name: UploadDate
Description: Date and time when the document was uploaded to the system. Auto-populated and read-only. Used for audit trail and document version tracking.

Name: Tenancy_LeaseRenewal
Description: Lease renewal history and negotiations

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the lease renewal record. System-generated GUID serving as the primary key. Used to track each renewal attempt, negotiation, and outcome for historical analysis.

Name: LeaseId
Description: Reference to the original lease agreement (Tenancy_Leases.Id). Links the renewal record to its parent lease for tracking renewal cycles and maintaining lease continuity.

Name: RenewalDate
Description: Date when the lease renewal takes effect. Must be on or after the current lease end date. Used for scheduling renewal notifications and calculating new lease terms.

Name: NewRentAmount
Description: Updated monthly rent amount for the renewed lease period. Must be zero or positive. Reflects any negotiated rent adjustments, escalations, or concessions applied during renewal.

Name: Tenancy_LeaseTermination
Description: Lease termination records and notice history

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the lease termination record. System-generated GUID serving as the primary key. Used to track termination proceedings, notices, and final settlement details.

Name: LeaseId
Description: Reference to the lease being terminated (Tenancy_Leases.Id). Links termination details to the specific lease agreement for audit trail and legal documentation purposes.

Name: TerminationDate
Description: Effective date when the lease terminates. Used to calculate notice periods, final rent proration, and move-out scheduling. Must comply with lease terms and local regulations.

Name: TerminationReason
Description: Reason for lease termination such as 'End of Term', 'Early Termination', 'Eviction', 'Mutual Agreement'. Required for legal compliance, reporting, and determining deposit handling procedures.

Name: Tenancy_LeaseAmendments
Description: Lease modifications and amendments

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the lease amendment record. System-generated GUID serving as the primary key. Tracks all modifications made to the original lease agreement over its lifetime.

Name: LeaseId
Description: Reference to the lease being amended (Tenancy_Leases.Id). Links the amendment to its parent lease for maintaining a complete history of all contractual changes.

Name: AmendmentDate
Description: Date when the amendment becomes effective. Used for chronological ordering of changes and determining which terms apply at any given point during the lease period.

Name: AmendmentDetails
Description: Detailed description of the lease modification including original terms, new terms, and reasons for change. Provides legal documentation of agreed-upon changes between landlord and tenant.

Name: Tenancy_Deposits
Description: Security and damage deposit management

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the deposit record. System-generated GUID serving as the primary key. Tracks individual deposits throughout their lifecycle from collection to refund or forfeiture.

Name: LeaseId
Description: Reference to the associated lease agreement (Tenancy_Leases.Id). Links the deposit to a specific tenancy for tracking obligations and determining refund eligibility upon lease end.

Name: DepositAmount
Description: Monetary value of the security deposit collected. Must be zero or positive. Typically equivalent to one or more months' rent as specified in lease terms and local regulations.

Name: DepositDate
Description: Date when the deposit was received from the tenant. Used for calculating interest accrual where required by law and tracking deposit holding duration for compliance purposes.

Name: Tenancy_DepositRefunds
Description: Deposit refund processing and deductions

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the deposit refund record. System-generated GUID serving as the primary key. Tracks refund processing, deductions, and final settlement amounts.

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to the parent deposit record (Tenancy_Deposits.Id). Establishes the relationship between the original deposit and its refund or deduction processing.

Name: RefundAmount
Description: Net amount refunded to the tenant after deductions. Must be zero or positive. Calculated as original deposit minus any legitimate deductions for damages, cleaning, or unpaid rent.

Name: RefundDate
Description: Date when the refund was processed and returned to the tenant. Must comply with legal timeframes for deposit return. Used for regulatory compliance tracking and audit purposes.

Name: Tenancy_DepositDisputes
Description: Deposit disputes and resolution tracking

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the deposit dispute record. System-generated GUID serving as the primary key. Tracks dispute proceedings, evidence, and resolution outcomes.

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to the parent deposit record (Tenancy_Deposits.Id). Links the dispute to the specific deposit being contested for case management and resolution tracking.

Name: DisputeReason
Description: Detailed description of the tenant's dispute regarding deposit deductions. Includes contested amounts, evidence references, and tenant's position on each deduction item.

Name: DisputeStatus
Description: Current status of the dispute such as 'Open', 'Under Review', 'Mediation', 'Resolved', 'Escalated to Court'. Used for workflow management and timeline compliance.

Name: Tenancy_RentBilling
Description: Monthly rent billing and invoicing

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the rent billing record. System-generated GUID serving as the primary key. Tracks each billing cycle's invoice generation, amounts due, and payment status.

Name: LeaseId
Description: Reference to the lease agreement (Tenancy_Leases.Id). Links billing to the active lease for determining rent amount, billing frequency, and payment terms.

Name: BillingPeriod
Description: The billing period covered such as 'January 2025', 'Q1 2025'. Identifies the specific timeframe for which rent is being charged. Used for invoice generation and payment matching.

Name: AmountDue
Description: Total rent amount due for the billing period. Must be zero or positive. Includes base rent plus any applicable charges, adjustments, or credits applied to the period.

Name: Tenancy_RentPayments
Description: Rent payment records and tracking

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the rent payment record. System-generated GUID serving as the primary key. Tracks individual payments, methods, and reconciliation with billing records.

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to the parent billing record (Tenancy_RentBilling.Id). Links payment to the specific invoice being paid for accurate accounts receivable reconciliation.

Name: PaymentAmount
Description: Amount paid by the tenant. Must be zero or positive. May be partial or full payment of the outstanding balance. Used for tracking payment history and balance calculations.

Name: PaymentDate
Description: Date when the payment was received or processed. Used for determining on-time vs late payment status, calculating late fees, and generating payment receipts.

Name: Tenancy_RentArrears
Description: Outstanding rent tracking and arrears management

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the rent arrears record. System-generated GUID serving as the primary key. Tracks overdue amounts, aging, and collection activities for each delinquent account.

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to the parent billing record (Tenancy_RentBilling.Id). Links arrears to the specific unpaid invoice for tracking collection efforts and payment plans.

Name: ArrearsAmount
Description: Total outstanding amount owed by the tenant. Must be zero or positive. Includes unpaid rent, accumulated late fees, and any other charges in arrears status.

Name: DaysOverdue
Description: Number of days the payment is past due. Calculated from the original due date. Used for aging reports, escalation triggers, and determining collection action thresholds.

Name: Tenancy_RentEscalation
Description: Rent escalation schedule and increases

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the rent escalation record. System-generated GUID serving as the primary key. Tracks scheduled rent increases as defined in the lease agreement.

Name: LeaseId
Description: Reference to the lease agreement (Tenancy_Leases.Id). Links the escalation schedule to the specific lease for applying rent increases according to contractual terms.

Name: EffectiveDate
Description: Date when the rent increase takes effect. Used for scheduling billing adjustments, sending advance notices, and updating the applicable rent amount for future billing cycles.

Name: IncreasePercentage
Description: Percentage increase to be applied to the current rent. Must be between 0 and 100. Used to calculate the new rent amount based on the escalation clause in the lease agreement.

Name: Tenancy_RentWaiver
Description: Rent waivers and concessions

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the rent waiver record. System-generated GUID serving as the primary key. Tracks approved concessions, discounts, and rent forgiveness for tenant hardship cases.

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to the parent billing record (Tenancy_RentBilling.Id). Links the waiver to the specific invoice where the concession is applied for accurate financial tracking.

Name: WaiverAmount
Description: Amount of rent being waived or discounted. Must be zero or positive. Reduces the tenant's payment obligation for the specified billing period due to approved concessions.

Name: WaiverReason
Description: Justification for granting the rent waiver such as 'Financial Hardship', 'Property Issue Compensation', 'Promotional Discount'. Required for audit trail and approval documentation.

Name: Tenancy_LateFees
Description: Late payment fees and penalties

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the late fee record. System-generated GUID serving as the primary key. Tracks penalty charges assessed for overdue rent payments per lease terms.

Name: ParentId
Description: Reference to the parent billing record (Tenancy_RentBilling.Id). Links the late fee to the specific overdue invoice for which the penalty was assessed.

Name: FeeAmount
Description: Monetary penalty charged for late payment. Must be zero or positive. Calculated based on lease terms, typically as a flat fee or percentage of overdue rent amount.

Name: AssessedDate
Description: Date when the late fee was assessed and added to the tenant's account. Used for tracking fee accrual, generating late payment notices, and compliance with grace period requirements.

Name: Tenancy_UtilitiesCharges
Description: Utility charges and billing (Electricity, Water, Gas)

Name: Id
Description: Unique identifier for the utility charge record. System-generated GUID serving as the primary key. Used to track individual utility charges across billing periods.

Name: LeaseId
Description: Reference to the lease agreement (Tenancy_Leases.Id). Establishes the relationship between the utility charge and the tenant's active lease for billing and accountability purposes.

Name: UtilityType
Description: Type of utility being charged such as 'Electricity', 'Water', 'Gas', 'Internet', 'Sewage'. Used for categorization and reporting of utility expenses per type.

Name: ChargeAmount
Description: Monetary amount charged for the utility. Must be zero or positive. Represents the actual billable amount for the specific utility type during the billing period.

Name: Tenancy_UtilitiesMeterReading
Description: Utility meter readings and consumption tracking - child table for detailed meter data

Name: Id
